The paper discusses the concept of Data Readiness Level (DRL) and proposes two metrics to measure it. The paper focuses on the properties of data that are relevant to data scientists, such as noisiness, believability, relevance, and coherence. These properties are commonly encountered in information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
